<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="535" pageId="7" pageNumber="534" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,750,2035]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="535" pageId="7" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,2010,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="534">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng et Jiang, 2003" authorityName="Zheng et Jiang" authorityYear="2003" box="[663,1177,2010,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cotysoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipalpulus">
<emphasis box="[663,933,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="534">Cotysoides albipalpulus</emphasis>
Zheng et Jiang, 
<number box="[1121,1177,2011,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="534" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1246,1313,2010,2035]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="534">China</collectingCountry>
(Guangxi) in the shape of the body and the relatively short pronotum, but differs from the latter in the shape of median carina of the pronotum and in the colour of the hind tibia (in 
<taxonomicName box="[765,939,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cotysoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipalpulus">
<emphasis box="[765,939,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="535">C. albipalpulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the median carina in profile sinuate and the hind tibia are black with two light rings).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
